    <etym xml:lang="ru">Закономерная перестановка из %i*afr-%i; восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>āfrī-</w></mentioned> (ожидаемого перехода %ir%i в %il%i перед %ii%i не
        произошло, вероятно, потому, что исходной была форма на сильной ступени: %iāfray%i-):
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>āfarīn, āfrīn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>āfrīn</w><gloss><q>хвала</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>nafrīn</w><gloss><q>проклятие</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*afrīw-(ʼʼpryw-),
                    *āfrīn(ʼʼpryn-)</w><gloss><q>благословлять</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><w>*āfrīwan(ʼʼprywn)</w><gloss><q>благословение</q></gloss></mentioned>,
        , <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/><w>*āfrīwan(ʼfrywn)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>aùrya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>āfrītī-</w><gloss><q>заклинание</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>благословение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>проклятие</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><w>āfrī-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %iā-%i + %ifrī-%i, <mentioned
                    xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>prī</w></mentioned>)</note><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="en"> (from %iā-%i + %ifrī-%i, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>prī</w></mentioned>)</note><gloss><q>пожелать кому (хорошего или
                    дурного)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w>āfrī-vācah</w><gloss><q>благословляющий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>проклинающий</q></gloss></mentioned>, (= <mentioned
            xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>arfæjy wac</w></mentioned>). Амбивалентность значения
        (‘благословлять’ — ‘проклинать’), утраченная в персидском, где для негативного значения
        создано новообразование (<mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>nafrīn</w></mentioned>), ясно
        еще чувствуется в осетинском, например %icæsti arfæ%i ‘заговор против дурного глаза’, см.
        выше. Однако позитивное значение и в осетинском получило преобладание, так что слову
        %iarfæ%i нередко противопоставляется <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lǧyst"/> ‘проклятие’. С
        корнем %ifrī-%i мы встречаемся еще в слове <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lymæn"/> ‘друг’ q.
                v.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 86</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>4</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>X 907</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">ОЯФ I 72, 581, 583
                сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">ОЯФ I 72, 581, 583
        ff.</biblScope></bibl></etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Regular alternation from %i*afr-%i; goes back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>āfrī-</w></mentioned> (there were no alterantion of %ir%i to %il%i before
        %ii%i, probably because of the fact that the strong grade form was initial: %iāfray%i-):
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>āfarīn, āfrīn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>āfrīn</w><gloss><q>praise</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>nafrīn</w><gloss><q>curse</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*afrīw-(ʼʼpryw-),
                *āfrīn(ʼʼpryn-)</w><gloss><q>bless</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><w>*āfrīwan(ʼʼprywn)</w><gloss><q>blessing</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="xpr"><lang/><w>*āfrīwan(ʼfrywn)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><lang/><w>aùrya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><lang/><w>āfrītī-</w><gloss><q>incantation</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>blessing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>curse</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><w>āfrī-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %iā-%i + %ifrī-%i, <mentioned
                    xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>prī</w></mentioned>)</note><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="en"> (from %iā-%i + %ifrī-%i, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>prī</w></mentioned>)</note><gloss><q>wish smb. (good or
                evil)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w>āfrī-vācah</w><gloss><q>blessing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>cursing</q></gloss></mentioned>, (= <mentioned xml:lang="os"
                ><lang/><w>arfæjy wac</w></mentioned>). Ambiguity of meaning (‘bless’ — ‘curse’),
        lost in Persian, where a new derivative was created for negative meaning (<mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>nafrīn</w></mentioned>), is also available in Ossetic, e. g.
        %icæsti arfæ%i ‘spell against the evil eye’, see above. However, the positive meaning has
        become prevalent in Ossetic, so the word %iarfæ%i is often opposed to <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_lǧyst"/> ‘curse’. The stem %ifrī-%i can also be found in the word <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_lymæn"/> ‘friend’ q. v.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 86</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>4</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>X 907</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">ОЯФ I 72, 581, 583
                сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">ОЯФ I 72, 581, 583
        ff.</biblScope></bibl></etym>
